      • flushToFileStore

        protected void flushToFileStore()
                         throws IOException
        Called before the cell about to be serialized. Subclasses may override it to make sure the content is sync'ed with the file (e.g. in-memory content is written to the FileStore).

        This method is also called when the file underlying object is copied into a another context (e.g. persisted outside the scope of the corresponding workflow).

        Throws:
        IOException - If unable to flush.

        Parameters:
